Sentencas: Miniaturized solid oxide fuel cells are fabricated on a photostructurable glass ceramic substrate (Foturan) by thin film and micromachining techniques.
Titulo: Micro Solid Oxide Fuel Cells on Glass Ceramic Substrates

Sentencas: The anode is a sputtered platinum film and the cathode is made of a spray pyrolysis (SP)-deposited lanthanum strontium cobalt iron oxide (LSCF), a sputtered platinum film and platinum paste.
Titulo: Micro Solid Oxide Fuel Cells on Glass Ceramic Substrates

Sentencas: A single-layer of yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) made by pulsed laser deposition (PLD) and a bilayer of PLD-YSZ and SP-YSZ are used as electrolytes.
Titulo: Micro Solid Oxide Fuel Cells on Glass Ceramic Substrates

Sentencas: The total thickness of all layers is less than 1 mu m and the cell is a free-standing membrane with a diameter up to 200 mu m.
Titulo: Micro Solid Oxide Fuel Cells on Glass Ceramic Substrates

Sentencas: The electrolyte resistance and the sum of polarization resistances of the anode and cathode are measured between 400 and 600 C by impedance spectroscopy and direct current (DC) techniques.
Titulo: Micro Solid Oxide Fuel Cells on Glass Ceramic Substrates

Sentencas: The contribution of the electrolyte resistance to the total cell resistance is negligible for all cells.
Titulo: Micro Solid Oxide Fuel Cells on Glass Ceramic Substrates

Sentencas: The area-specific polarization resistance of the electrodes decreases for different cathode materials in the order of Pt paste > sputtered Pt > LSCF.
Titulo: Micro Solid Oxide Fuel Cells on Glass Ceramic Substrates

Sentencas: The open circuit voltages (OCVs) of the single-layer electrolyte cells ranges from 0.91 to 0.56 V at 550 degrees C.
Titulo: Micro Solid Oxide Fuel Cells on Glass Ceramic Substrates

Sentencas: No electronic leakage in the PLD-YSZ electrolyte is found by in-plane and cross-plane electrical conductivity measurements and the low OCV is attributed to gas leakage through pinholes in the columnar microstructure of the electrolyte.
Titulo: Micro Solid Oxide Fuel Cells on Glass Ceramic Substrates

Sentencas: By using a bilayer electrolyte of PLD-YSZ and SP-YSZ, an OCV of 1.06 V is obtained and the maximum power density reaches 152 mW cm(-2) at 550 degrees C.
Titulo: Micro Solid Oxide Fuel Cells on Glass Ceramic Substrates
